claim.claim-text:
1. A machine for controllably flying a flag in the absence of the natural wind, comprising:
a long cylindrical centrifugal fan and shaft assembly driven by a motor mounted inside a housing of a base unit by means of pulleys and a serpentine belt;
a tubular windpipe attached to the base unit and surrounding the fan and shaft assembly, an airfoil, and a flag pole,
wherein a shaft of the fan and shaft assembly is rotatably supported by bearings;
wherein the airfoil is positioned between a fan of the fan and shaft assembly and the flag pole and has an adjustable angle of attack, altering air blowing past it and thereby permitting the controlled manipulation of the attitude of a flag mounted on the flag pole.
